The effect of heparin, mainly LMW heparin, is reported by Tang et al. (
 9) showing reduced mortality in cases with coagulopathy treated with heparin compared to patients who had coagulopathy not treated with heparin (40.0 vs. 64, 2%, respectively; 
 p = 0.029). Heparin exhibits anti-inflammatory effects by neutralizing DAMPs to protect endothelial cells and reduce pulmonary edema and vascular loss.
